The paper proposes a new neural architecture for next item recommendation, which is a subfield of recommender systems. The model utilizes multi-scale convolutional features and recurrent cells to capture the recurrent relations between different kinds of local features. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Among these, cs.LG and cs.IR are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the machine learning and recommendation aspects of the paper.
